WEBVTT

00:14.120 --> 00:15.120
<i> Nightfall…</i>

00:19.240 --> 00:22.880
<i>reveals our planet's connection</i>
<i>to the universe.</i>

00:28.160 --> 00:29.560
<i>A shooting star.</i>

00:31.200 --> 00:34.480
<i>Ancient rock from the depths of space</i>…

00:38.680 --> 00:39.880
<i>falling to Earth.</i>

00:50.320 --> 00:54.880
<i>Inside it are the chemical elements</i>
<i>that built our universe.</i>

01:10.480 --> 01:12.160
<i>For countless generations,</i>

01:13.000 --> 01:16.160
<i>sea turtles have roamed the oceans,</i>

01:16.760 --> 01:20.480
<i>gathering cosmic elements</i>
<i>in the food they eat.</i>

01:24.160 --> 01:27.720
<i>And as they've done</i>
<i>for hundreds of millions of years…</i>

01:33.880 --> 01:35.560
<i>every new generation</i>

01:37.520 --> 01:40.360
<i>recycles this same stardust…</i>

01:43.320 --> 01:45.200
<i>to produce the next.</i>

01:53.800 --> 01:55.400
<i>Born in The Big Bang</i>…

01:56.840 --> 01:59.400
…<i>and forged in the hearts of stars…</i>

02:01.640 --> 02:05.600
<i>…90 chemical elements</i>
<i>have created everything.</i>

02:08.120 --> 02:10.680
<i>Endlessly recycled and reconfigured</i>

02:11.680 --> 02:15.160
<i>throughout the entire history</i>
<i>of the universe.</i>

02:18.240 --> 02:19.480
<i>And now…</i>

02:21.640 --> 02:23.440
<i>using the same elements,</i>

02:24.760 --> 02:27.400
<i>each new turtle begins a life cycle…</i>

02:33.960 --> 02:37.600
<i>…that mirrors the lives of the stars.</i>

03:18.400 --> 03:20.960
<i>On Australia's Great Barrier Reef…</i>

03:28.680 --> 03:31.120
…<i>something magical has happened.</i>

03:37.880 --> 03:40.280
<i>After 50 days beneath the sand,</i>

03:41.480 --> 03:46.880
<i>chemical elements</i>
<i>from across the cosmos have created life.</i>

03:49.280 --> 03:52.480
<i>Combining to form the next generation</i>

03:53.480 --> 03:54.960
<i>of green sea turtles.</i>

04:18.400 --> 04:22.400
<i>The eggs have now exhausted their supply</i>
<i>of life-giving elements.</i>

04:39.760 --> 04:45.160
<i>And today, the baby turtles</i>
<i>will take their first taste of air.</i>

04:59.080 --> 05:03.000
<i>And as her brothers and sisters</i>
<i>scramble to make it to the water…</i>

05:08.600 --> 05:09.800
<i>a little female…</i>

05:12.560 --> 05:14.400
<i>is last to be born.</i>

05:20.120 --> 05:22.160
<i>In order to grow to adulthood,</i>

05:23.880 --> 05:27.720
<i>she will need to harvest chemical elements</i>
<i>from across the ocean.</i>

05:36.800 --> 05:38.400
<i>It's a dangerous journey…</i>

05:41.120 --> 05:43.280
<i>…with treachery at every turn.</i>

05:50.400 --> 05:51.880
<i>But for the baby turtles,</i>

05:53.200 --> 05:56.360
<i>the call of the ocean is irresistible.</i>

06:09.840 --> 06:11.200
<i>From a nest of 100,</i>

06:12.320 --> 06:14.880
<i>sometimes only one will survive.</i>

06:18.680 --> 06:20.840
<i>Sometimes none.</i>

07:13.560 --> 07:15.080
<i>But despite the risk,</i>

07:17.240 --> 07:19.040
<i>the little female knows</i>

07:19.560 --> 07:21.880
<i>she must make it to the water.</i>

07:59.880 --> 08:01.320
<i>She spots an opening…</i>

08:04.680 --> 08:05.920
<i>and takes her chance.</i>

08:20.880 --> 08:21.720
<i>Today…</i>

08:24.400 --> 08:25.720
<i>she's a lucky one.</i>

08:29.080 --> 08:34.400
<i>The hatchling won't stop swimming</i>
<i>until she has left the reef far behind.</i>

08:47.120 --> 08:51.520
<i>Safely past the predators</i>
<i>that gather in the shallow coastal waters,</i>

08:52.720 --> 08:55.920
<i>she'll disappear into the great void</i>
<i>of the open ocean</i>…

09:03.200 --> 09:07.600
<i>to spend her childhood feeding on atoms.</i>

09:14.240 --> 09:20.920
<i>Atoms whose origins go back through</i>
<i>the entire life of the cosmos.</i>

09:26.640 --> 09:30.040
<i>To the time our universe</i>

09:30.640 --> 09:32.440
<i>was in its infancy.</i>

09:48.000 --> 09:53.080
<i>Expanding from nothing</i>
<i>to everything in an instant.</i>

09:56.280 --> 09:59.800
<i>Our universe was born in The Big Bang.</i>

10:07.400 --> 10:08.280
<i>At first,</i>

10:09.040 --> 10:11.800
<i>it was nothing but a hot, dense fog.</i>

10:19.080 --> 10:21.480
<i>But as it continued to expand…</i>

10:24.360 --> 10:26.000
<i>the fog began to cool.</i>

10:29.400 --> 10:32.040
<i>And on the tiniest scale imaginable…</i>

10:33.600 --> 10:35.960
<i>…something astounding began to occur.</i>

10:42.000 --> 10:45.400
<i>The first atoms condensed out of the fog.</i>

10:50.120 --> 10:52.400
<i>Atoms of hydrogen.</i>

10:56.040 --> 10:59.600
<i>The very first element in the universe.</i>

11:06.640 --> 11:07.800
<i>And in the ocean,</i>

11:08.680 --> 11:11.920
<i>juvenile turtles are hunting it down.</i>

11:15.160 --> 11:17.480
<i>As they emerge from the blue</i>

11:17.560 --> 11:20.120
<i>to forage in the shallow waters</i>
<i>of the reef.</i>

11:24.920 --> 11:26.560
<i>This is Stella.</i>

11:27.760 --> 11:30.640
<i>One of the lucky ones</i>
<i>that made it off the beach</i>

11:31.280 --> 11:32.520
<i>and into the ocean.</i>

11:41.480 --> 11:44.680
<i>She's already more than 2,000 times</i>
<i>her hatching weight</i>

11:45.840 --> 11:46.880
<i>and growing fast.</i>

11:51.840 --> 11:55.360
<i>Feeding on creatures she's found drifting</i>
<i>in the open ocean,</i>

11:56.840 --> 11:59.880
<i>she's harvested one element</i>
<i>more than any other.</i>

12:08.640 --> 12:09.480
<i>Hydrogen.</i>

12:12.560 --> 12:16.800
<i>It makes up more than half</i>
<i>of all the atoms in the food she eats.</i>

12:20.800 --> 12:24.480
<i>And is the most abundant element</i>
<i>in all living things.</i>

12:28.600 --> 12:29.680
<i>From fish</i>

12:30.960 --> 12:32.200
<i>to invertebrates.</i>

12:38.960 --> 12:41.320
<i>Anemones and coral.</i>

12:54.440 --> 12:58.560
<i>Hydrogen atoms formed</i>
<i>at the dawn of the universe</i>

12:59.520 --> 13:03.200
<i>have been passed on from star to planet,</i>

13:04.320 --> 13:05.920
<i>planet to animal…</i>

13:08.320 --> 13:11.280
<i>and from prey to predator.</i>

13:22.080 --> 13:23.480
<i>Which means, for Stella,</i>

13:24.280 --> 13:27.000
<i>the waters around the reef</i>
<i>are full of danger.</i>

13:30.880 --> 13:33.920
<i>Tiger sharks, hungry for the same atoms,</i>

13:34.000 --> 13:37.000
<i>hunt sea turtles</i>
<i>throughout their adult lives.</i>

13:45.280 --> 13:48.560
<i>Stella's main defense is her trusty armor.</i>

13:52.280 --> 13:55.280
<i>Its bone toughened</i>
<i>with calcium and phosphorus.</i>

14:02.320 --> 14:05.320
<i>Elements that date back</i>
<i>to another pivotal moment…</i>

14:09.400 --> 14:11.280
<i>in the life of our universe.</i>

14:21.920 --> 14:25.680
<i>For the first 300 million years</i>
<i>after The Big Bang…</i>

14:28.080 --> 14:31.000
<i>there are no planets and no stars.</i>

14:34.080 --> 14:36.600
<i>The dark ages of the universe.</i>

14:42.360 --> 14:44.120
<i>Concealed in the gloom,</i>

14:44.640 --> 14:48.600
<i>vast tendrils</i>
<i>of hydrogen gas crisscross the cosmos.</i>

14:53.280 --> 14:55.560
<i>And then, incredibly,</i>

14:56.200 --> 14:58.680
<i>as they were drawn together by gravity…</i>

15:02.400 --> 15:04.520
<i>…the first stars were born.</i>

15:11.120 --> 15:13.000
<i>This is the cosmic dawn.</i>

15:16.720 --> 15:20.880
<i>The moment the lights came on.</i>

15:28.000 --> 15:30.680
<i>And deep within those first stars…</i>

15:34.880 --> 15:37.080
<i>a remarkable process began.</i>

15:42.800 --> 15:46.080
<i>Temperatures and pressures</i>
<i>were so extreme…</i>

15:48.080 --> 15:50.360
…<i>that new elements were created.</i>

15:52.520 --> 15:56.400
<i>Atoms of hydrogen</i>
<i>were forced together to make helium.</i>

15:58.800 --> 16:01.880
<i>As they fused, energy was released.</i>

16:04.520 --> 16:09.200
<i>Creating a chain reaction that produced</i>
<i>increasingly heavier elements.</i>

16:12.320 --> 16:15.640
<i>Including those essential for life.</i>

16:17.640 --> 16:21.360
<i>Three helium atoms combined</i>
<i>to make carbon.</i>

16:26.800 --> 16:29.480
<i>The element on which all life is based.</i>

16:31.760 --> 16:34.560
<i>Carbon and helium made oxygen.</i>

16:36.120 --> 16:37.400
<i>The air we breathe.</i>

16:39.680 --> 16:42.880
<i>Oxygen atoms combined to make phosphorus.</i>

16:44.920 --> 16:47.160
<i>Then silicon and calcium.</i>

16:50.200 --> 16:52.800
<i>The elements</i>
<i>that make up every living thing</i>

16:54.320 --> 16:58.800
<i>were created in the hearts</i>
<i>of the very first stars.</i>

17:31.000 --> 17:31.880
<i>For Stella,</i>

17:33.160 --> 17:35.040
<i>some elements are so important</i>…

17:38.600 --> 17:41.080
…<i>she'll travel great distances</i>
<i>to find them.</i>

17:51.600 --> 17:56.000
<i>The warm, shallow waters</i>
<i>between Australia and Papua New Guinea</i>

17:57.360 --> 17:59.800
<i>are a paradise of vibrant seagrass.</i>

18:04.200 --> 18:06.680
<i>The prairies of the ocean.</i>

18:16.120 --> 18:21.960
<i>Stella has traveled all the way here</i>
<i>to access their magic ingredients.</i>

18:32.560 --> 18:34.000
<i>As it grows,</i>

18:34.080 --> 18:37.200
<i>seagrass absorbs elements from outer space</i>

18:37.920 --> 18:40.680
<i>that have found their way</i>
<i>to the ocean floor.</i>

18:43.880 --> 18:48.040
<i>Burgeoning fronds</i>
<i>rich in calcium and phosphorus</i>

18:49.760 --> 18:53.280
<i>provide Stella</i>
<i>with precisely the minerals she needs</i>

18:55.080 --> 18:58.320
<i>to build and sustain her protective shell.</i>

19:01.880 --> 19:06.000
<i>Hardening her armor for the trials ahead.</i>

19:14.400 --> 19:16.960
<i>Stella will spend her adolescent years</i>

19:17.680 --> 19:19.200
<i>searching the ocean</i>

19:20.920 --> 19:24.240
<i>for atoms born in the stars.</i>

19:33.240 --> 19:35.080
<i>Her journey toward maturity…</i>

19:37.320 --> 19:40.800
<i>paralleled in the story of our universe.</i>

19:45.680 --> 19:48.920
<i>Because three billion years</i>
<i>after The Big Bang…</i>

19:53.880 --> 19:56.680
<i>…the universe was also coming of age.</i>

20:02.640 --> 20:08.440
<i>It was entering an incredibly active phase</i>
<i>of star formation.</i>

20:12.200 --> 20:13.240
<i>As they grew,</i>

20:13.960 --> 20:17.280
<i>stars were pulled together</i>
<i>into vast galaxies.</i>

20:20.080 --> 20:21.800
<i>Like our Milky Way.</i>

20:25.000 --> 20:26.880
<i>And within those galaxies,</i>

20:28.160 --> 20:30.840
<i>the chemical elements each star produced…</i>

20:34.520 --> 20:40.960
<i>…were transformed into planets and moons.</i>

20:49.920 --> 20:51.480
<i>After billions of years,</i>

20:53.320 --> 20:58.880
<i>chemical elements have matured</i>
<i>into the Earth we know today.</i>

21:23.080 --> 21:25.800
<i>Stella is now fully grown herself.</i>

21:29.880 --> 21:31.240
<i>Over a meter long,</i>

21:32.280 --> 21:35.600
<i>she has a thick shell</i>
<i>covered in green algae.</i>

21:39.240 --> 21:42.400
<i>Ideal camouflage for cruising coral reefs.</i>

21:46.600 --> 21:49.120
<i>She is now at one with the ocean.</i>

21:55.800 --> 21:57.440
<i>Atoms from the stars</i>

21:59.320 --> 22:02.600
<i>perfectly adapted to life at sea.</i>

22:11.000 --> 22:13.120
<i>Just one example of life on Earth…</i>

22:15.280 --> 22:18.320
<i>exquisitely shaped from the cosmos.</i>

22:35.560 --> 22:39.000
<i>Stella is now ready</i>
<i>for the next stage of her life.</i>

22:43.680 --> 22:47.000
<i>Because she's about</i>
<i>to become a mother herself.</i>

22:50.200 --> 22:51.320
<i>Inside her body…</i>

22:53.960 --> 22:56.480
<i>she's carrying a clutch of 100 eggs.</i>

22:58.280 --> 23:01.080
<i>The first of many</i>
<i>she'll have over her lifetime.</i>

23:03.680 --> 23:07.880
<i>Her own precious cargo of stardust.</i>

23:15.760 --> 23:17.120
<i>All across the reef,</i>

23:18.360 --> 23:20.720
<i>atoms are being assembled into new life.</i>

23:25.480 --> 23:30.160
<i>Creating one of the richest ecosystems</i>
<i>on Earth.</i>

23:35.920 --> 23:38.000
<i>But our planet…</i>

23:41.320 --> 23:42.400
…<i>is an outlier.</i>

23:44.960 --> 23:47.120
<i>In the rest of the solar system,</i>

23:47.200 --> 23:49.160
<i>the very same elements</i>

23:49.240 --> 23:54.000
<i>have created worlds</i>
<i>far less suited to life.</i>

23:59.920 --> 24:01.320
<i>Closest to the sun,</i>

24:02.080 --> 24:05.000
<i>Mercury is a planet rich in carbon.</i>

24:07.880 --> 24:09.680
<i>But rather than creating life,</i>

24:11.560 --> 24:13.800
<i>the carbon is baked into its crust.</i>

24:16.160 --> 24:19.920
<i>On a world scorched by starlight.</i>

24:22.520 --> 24:26.440
<i>While in the farthest reaches</i>
<i>of the solar system,</i>

24:26.520 --> 24:28.560
<i>Neptune's freezing temperatures</i>

24:29.480 --> 24:33.520
<i>cause carbon and hydrogen</i>
<i>to form clouds of methane.</i>

24:36.680 --> 24:40.880
<i>The suffocating gas</i>
<i>that gives it its brilliant blue.</i>

24:46.640 --> 24:47.960
<i>And even on Mars,</i>

24:49.160 --> 24:51.960
<i>a planet with all the same ingredients</i>
<i>as Earth…</i>

24:54.320 --> 24:56.880
<i>the lack of an oxygen-rich atmosphere</i>

24:57.520 --> 25:00.880
<i>means complex life couldn't survive here.</i>

25:07.800 --> 25:12.080
<i>Only on Earth are conditions just right.</i>

25:18.320 --> 25:19.320
<i>But even here,</i>

25:20.120 --> 25:22.280
<i>competition for elements is fierce.</i>

25:24.200 --> 25:25.040
<i>And danger…</i>

25:27.560 --> 25:29.040
…<i>is never far away.</i>

25:44.880 --> 25:48.400
<i>Luckily, Stella has become</i>
<i>an expert at hide-and-seek.</i>

26:29.920 --> 26:31.400
<i>Safe for now…</i>

26:34.320 --> 26:37.320
<i>Stella faces the biggest challenge</i>
<i>of her life.</i>

26:39.520 --> 26:42.280
<i>To return to the Great Barrier Reef</i>

26:43.920 --> 26:45.600
<i>and the island of her birth…</i>

26:49.480 --> 26:51.880
<i>to lay her own eggs in the sand.</i>

26:58.880 --> 27:01.440
<i>But a lifetime spent wandering the ocean</i>

27:02.200 --> 27:05.600
<i>means she's now 2,000 kilometers away.</i>

27:09.840 --> 27:11.520
<i>How Stella navigates home</i>

27:12.160 --> 27:14.760
<i>is one of the wonders</i>
<i>of the natural world.</i>

27:21.400 --> 27:22.760
<i>Deep within the Earth,</i>

27:23.600 --> 27:26.600
<i>our planet's core generates</i>
<i>a magnetic field…</i>

27:28.840 --> 27:33.880
<i>which gives every place on its surface</i>
<i>a unique magnetic signature.</i>

27:37.560 --> 27:39.120
<i>When she hatched,</i>

27:39.200 --> 27:43.520
<i>her island's signature</i>
<i>was imprinted in Stella's brain.</i>

27:46.200 --> 27:48.200
<i>And to find her way back,</i>

27:48.280 --> 27:51.600
<i>she'll rely on</i>
<i>yet another chemical element.</i>

27:53.760 --> 27:56.880
<i>One that connects her</i>
<i>to the planet's core.</i>

28:00.400 --> 28:05.080
<i>An element that's only created</i>
<i>when stars die.</i>

28:10.680 --> 28:12.720
<i>In a nearby part of the galaxy,</i>

28:13.720 --> 28:15.680
<i>two and a half million years ago,</i>

28:16.720 --> 28:20.520
<i>a dramatic change took place</i>
<i>in the core of a giant star.</i>

28:25.280 --> 28:29.360
<i>For all its life,</i>
<i>it had been powered by nuclear fusion.</i>

28:35.880 --> 28:37.200
<i>The energy released</i>…

28:39.040 --> 28:41.440
…<i>creating heavier and heavier elements.</i>

28:45.200 --> 28:48.120
<i>Until the core became so hot,</i>

28:48.640 --> 28:49.880
<i>it started creating</i>…

28:51.640 --> 28:52.480
…<i>iron.</i>

28:55.360 --> 28:58.200
<i>Which caused a fundamental change</i>
<i>to take place.</i>

29:03.080 --> 29:06.360
<i>Because making iron</i>
<i>doesn't release energy.</i>

29:07.880 --> 29:09.160
<i>It consumes it.</i>

29:15.880 --> 29:18.360
<i>As more and more</i>
<i>of the metal was produced,</i>

29:19.240 --> 29:22.760
<i>it spread through the core like a disease.</i>

29:27.160 --> 29:29.160
<i>Feeding off the star's heat.</i>

29:33.880 --> 29:34.880
<i>Throttling it.</i>

29:46.280 --> 29:48.560
<i>With no heat source to hold it up.</i>

29:52.840 --> 29:54.400
<i>From this moment onward…</i>

29:57.480 --> 29:59.680
<i>…the star was doomed.</i>

30:11.600 --> 30:16.200
<i>The resulting explosion shone</i>
<i>with the brightness of 10 billion suns.</i>

30:22.000 --> 30:27.080
<i>A supernova which propelled</i>
<i>iron-rich dust across the galaxy.</i>

30:35.120 --> 30:38.120
<i>All the way to our planet.</i>

30:43.160 --> 30:44.280
<i>And even now,</i>

30:45.280 --> 30:50.280
<i>100 tons of stardust enters</i>
<i>Earth's atmosphere every day.</i>

30:53.080 --> 30:56.800
<i>Some left over</i>
<i>from the formation of the solar system.</i>

31:00.600 --> 31:04.480
<i>Some blown here from distant supernovas.</i>

31:08.400 --> 31:13.600
<i>A direct link</i>
<i>between our planet and the stars.</i>

31:19.680 --> 31:21.960
<i>And it's the iron in this dust</i>

31:22.520 --> 31:25.400
<i>that allows Stella to find her way.</i>

31:33.520 --> 31:35.200
<i>Because deep in her brain…</i>

31:38.280 --> 31:43.600
<i>…specialized cells are thought</i>
<i>to contain crystals of magnetite.</i>

31:44.520 --> 31:48.760
<i>An iron-rich mineral that aligns itself</i>
<i>to the Earth's magnetic field.</i>

31:52.760 --> 31:53.680
<i>A compass,</i>

31:55.560 --> 31:57.680
<i>pointing her in the right direction.</i>

32:05.440 --> 32:11.680
<i>Allowing Stella to find</i>
<i>the unique magnetic fingerprint of home.</i>

32:19.480 --> 32:22.680
<i>And so an element forged in a supernova…</i>

32:30.360 --> 32:34.280
<i>…will now guide her across kilometers</i>
<i>of featureless ocean.</i>

32:48.600 --> 32:49.920
<i>Back to the island…</i>

32:53.800 --> 32:55.480
<i>on which she was born.</i>

33:08.120 --> 33:12.040
<i>But there are other creatures</i>
<i>with magnetic homing abilities.</i>

33:14.680 --> 33:16.480
<i>The tiger sharks have it too.</i>

33:19.600 --> 33:22.280
<i>And it's leading them back</i>
<i>to the same island.</i>

33:26.560 --> 33:28.920
<i>Because for a few months every year,</i>

33:29.000 --> 33:32.600
<i>thousands of female turtles come here</i>
<i>to lay their eggs.</i>

33:34.600 --> 33:37.880
<i>It's the largest gathering</i>
<i>of green sea turtles</i>

33:37.960 --> 33:39.960
<i>anywhere on the planet.</i>

33:45.600 --> 33:47.320
<i>And as they come to shore,</i>

33:49.080 --> 33:50.320
<i>the feeding begins.</i>

34:03.800 --> 34:06.160
<i>Stella must wait for the right moment…</i>

34:08.840 --> 34:10.040
<i>to find an opening</i>…

34:12.160 --> 34:14.080
<i>and avoid the onslaught.</i>

34:32.080 --> 34:33.800
<i>When the danger has passed…</i>

34:37.440 --> 34:39.080
<i>she finally swims ashore.</i>

34:52.280 --> 34:53.880
<i>After an epic journey…</i>

34:57.080 --> 34:59.240
<i>Stella emerges onto the sand</i>

35:00.840 --> 35:03.320
<i>she last touched as a hatchling.</i>

35:28.040 --> 35:30.920
<i>The elements she spent</i>
<i>a lifetime collecting…</i>

35:36.600 --> 35:39.160
<i>are now safely delivered into the sand.</i>

35:45.240 --> 35:46.960
<i>Stella's mission is complete,</i>

35:47.520 --> 35:49.240
<i>and she returns to the ocean…</i>

35:52.880 --> 35:56.600
<i>to begin gathering stardust once more.</i>

36:00.480 --> 36:01.800
<i>The cycle of her life</i>

36:03.640 --> 36:06.520
<i>mirroring the grandest cycle of all.</i>

36:08.440 --> 36:11.920
<i>The lives and deaths of the stars.</i>

36:22.480 --> 36:25.600
<i>Because far away across the galaxy,</i>

36:27.000 --> 36:29.680
<i>the ashes of countless supernovas</i>

36:29.760 --> 36:34.480
<i>have come together to form a giant nebula.</i>

36:41.280 --> 36:44.480
<i>A cloud of stardust</i>
<i>tens of light-years across.</i>

36:48.120 --> 36:52.600
<i>And buried within it are places</i>
<i>where the next generation of stars</i>

36:53.840 --> 36:55.280
<i>are beginning to form.</i>

37:06.800 --> 37:08.400
<i>Called proplyds.</i>

37:10.400 --> 37:12.880
<i>They're like vast cosmic eggs.</i>

37:15.000 --> 37:17.680
<i>Each one bigger than our solar system.</i>

37:23.720 --> 37:26.640
<i>Inside their shells of ionized gas,</i>

37:28.560 --> 37:31.480
<i>the force of gravity</i>
<i>is pulling stardust together.</i>

37:38.880 --> 37:42.400
<i>And the stardust inside Stella's eggs…</i>

37:45.440 --> 37:47.560
<i>is also beginning to take shape.</i>

37:56.200 --> 38:01.800
<i>As the elements she collected</i>
<i>are being transformed…</i>

38:08.280 --> 38:11.800
<i>into something that's starting</i>
<i>to resemble a tiny creature.</i>

38:24.280 --> 38:25.640
<i>And within the proplyd…</i>

38:27.840 --> 38:30.240
<i>gases like hydrogen and helium…</i>

38:33.120 --> 38:35.680
<i>…are feeding an embryonic star.</i>

38:44.880 --> 38:46.680
<i>And what was once an embryo…</i>

38:49.080 --> 38:51.080
<i>is now a tiny turtle</i>…

38:55.200 --> 38:58.880
<i>with shell, flippers, and beak.</i>

39:02.880 --> 39:04.680
<i>Elements reimagined…</i>

39:08.080 --> 39:10.280
<i>for a life at sea.</i>

39:15.160 --> 39:16.120
<i>In the proplyd,</i>

39:17.000 --> 39:20.200
<i>the new star's development</i>
<i>is also nearing completion.</i>

39:21.480 --> 39:24.800
<i>Reborn from the ashes</i>
<i>of the previous generation,</i>

39:26.120 --> 39:30.000
<i>its light now reveals a family</i>
<i>of growing planets in orbit.</i>

39:34.200 --> 39:35.320
<i>New worlds.</i>

39:36.240 --> 39:40.280
<i>But perhaps, new possibilities for life.</i>

39:48.280 --> 39:49.920
<i>And beneath the sand,</i>

39:51.240 --> 39:52.760
<i>the same stardust,</i>

39:54.080 --> 39:58.800
<i>passed down through countless generations</i>
<i>of stars and turtles…</i>

40:00.880 --> 40:03.200
<i>will start yet another journey.</i>

40:08.160 --> 40:09.560
<i>Each new life</i>

40:11.080 --> 40:15.400
<i>directly connected</i>
<i>to the origin of the universe.</i>

40:20.840 --> 40:26.400
<i>Each new story beginning</i>
<i>at the end of the last.</i>

40:34.880 --> 40:38.880
<i>And so,</i>
<i>the story of our universe continues…</i>

40:40.760 --> 40:43.000
<i>…with Earth's most precious resource…</i>

40:46.280 --> 40:47.120
…<i>water.</i>

40:48.920 --> 40:52.800
<i>And a family of elephants</i>
<i>on a dangerous mission to find it.</i>

40:57.000 --> 40:59.360
<i>Their journey every bit as extraordinary</i>…

41:01.680 --> 41:06.440
…<i>as water's journey across the vastness</i>
<i>of space to our planet.</i>

41:10.640 --> 41:13.840
<i>But why is Earth the only world</i>
<i>in the solar system</i>

41:14.840 --> 41:17.240
<i>whose surface</i>
<i>is covered with liquid water?</i>

41:18.600 --> 41:21.960
<i>And why is it so essential for life?</i>
